  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2008-11 USAID/Food for Peace Multi-Year Assistance Program (MYAP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Households in the most vulnerable watersheds in three of the most food insecure regions of Burundi</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MYAP will achieve its objectives through a holistic response: community-based activities to improve nutrition through HEARTH and community-based therapeutic care, child health through C-IMCI, hygiene using a proven methodology such as PHAST, access to food through agro-enterprise development and SILC, protection of natural resources via Food-for-Assets and improved natural resource management, and strengthened resilience through early warning systems and preparedness planning.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to better health, nutrition and potable water, increase livelihood capabilities through environmentally-sustainable agricultural production and off- and on-farm income generation, and improve community resilience and capacity to respond to shocks.</narrative>
  </description>
